This is a guide to defeating [[Commander Zilyana]], the [[Saradominist]] general in the [[God Wars Dungeon]].

While Commander Zilyana has an equal amount of resistance to all attacks, [[Magic]] (apart from the [[Tumeken's shadow]]) is generally impractical here due to the lack of defence provided by magic armour and unnecessary [[runes|rune]] costs.

==Requirements==
*Completion of [[Death Plateau]] and the start of [[Troll Stronghold]] to the point where you defeat [[Dad]]
*Alternatively, [[Ghommal's hilt]] can be used to teleport to [[Trollheim]] without requiring either quest
*One [[rope]] is required to access the [[God Wars Dungeon]] for the ''first'' time.
*Two (additional) ropes are required to navigate [[Saradomin's Encampment]] for the ''first'' time.
*Level 70 [[Agility]] is required to access Saradomin's Encampment (cannot be boosted).
*Level 37 [[Prayer]] to activate [[Protect from Magic]].

==Strategy==
===General Strategy===
Similarly to [[Kree'arra]], many players prefer using an [[ecumenical key]] to skip kill count. Although Saradominist kill count is considered to be somewhat quick, this is only partially true if the player has 83 [[Slayer]], as Saradominist [[spiritual warrior]]s and [[spiritual mage|mages]] are aggressive towards Zamorakian followers. The remaining Saradominist followers are passive and will only attack in self-defence. 

[[Commander Zilyana|Zilyana]] attacks with both melee and magic. Pray [[Protect from Magic]] while killing Zilyana if using ranged or [[Protect from Missiles]] if using mage. If done correctly the only damage you should take is from the range or mage minion, respectively. Although her max hit is relatively low, with her melee attacks dealing up to 27 damage and her magic dealing 10-20 damage, she makes up for this with an attack speed of 2 (1.2 seconds). Combined with her tremendous accuracy, this makes fighting her in melee range extremely dangerous, as the precise attacks and rapid attack speed will cause a swift death for her target. Like Graardor and K'ril however, Zilyana can only attack when in melee distance of a player.

Zilyana has three bodyguards; [[Bree]], [[Growler]] and [[Starlight]], who use ranged, magic and melee with maximum hits of 16, 16 and 15 damage respectively. Her bodyguards are significantly weaker compared to the other generals', but they still should not be underestimated.

The [[Safespot#Kiting|kiting]] method should be used when fighting Zilyana, as her chamber is quite large. This means that damage will only be incurred from the bodyguard that the player is not protecting against, as Starlight and Zilyana will not be able to reach the player unless they stop moving. The most common method involves running around the chamber, though there are advanced methods that reduce or even negate the need for stamina potions, even with low Agility levels.

[[File:Zilyana Hit-and-Run.png|frame|Use the hit-and-run tactic on Zilyana.]]

====Ranging====
For players ranging Zilyana, the most common methods are to either use a [[crossbow]] with enchanted diamond bolts, full crystal armour with a [[Bow of faerdhinen]], or a [[twisted bow]]. A [[toxic blowpipe]] and a [[serpentine helm]] switch, while optional, are helpful in envenoming the bodyguards, as it will guarantee that they will be envenomed upon hit. This will help whittle down their health while Zilyana is being killed, especially if not using a twisted bow.

====Bow of Faerdhinen No Stamina====
This advanced ranged setup allows players to kill Commander Zilyana without using [[stamina potion]]s. This method requires following a specific pattern in order to attack Zilyana up to 12 times without getting attacked in the process, while also conserving energy. The player should always pray protect from magic while killing Zilyana.

'''For every kill except the first kill:'''
# Start on blue tile labelled 1 and attack twice.
# Run to tile 2 and attack once
# Click on yellow tile (your character will automatically walk this tile) before running to tile 3 and attacking once
# Click on the next yellow, then run to tile 4 and attack again. On the last tile (12), attack and run to tile 2 and restart the process
# '''Turn off run once Zilyana is dead'''

Attack on every red tile, while walking all the yellow tiles. This allows your character to conserve and restore energy while also allowing you to stay out of range of Commander Zilyana.

Assuming the player has about 80 Agility, around 10-12 run energy is used per lap.

The bodyguards Bree, Starlight and Growler all have a chance to drop summer pies which can be used to restore 10% run energy per bite (total 20%).

'''For the first kill'''
# Start on green tile 1, attack once and run to the green tile 2
# Run to red tile 4 and carry on like you would for all normal kills.

